Monday August 19th 2013 2:46 pm -04:00,Hi Connor  As a simplified explanation there is a mapping of numbers to characters. One example of this is ASCII (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ASCII#ASCII_printable_characters). The ord() function allows us to ask Python what number is associated with a character.  There is a reciprocal function called chr() that takes a number and gives us a character.For example:>>> ord(A)65>>> chr(65)A>>>Byrne G, Resolved,6
