Tuesday August 20th 2013 1:31 pm -04:00,David is correct there is no real limit on the length of a variable name I have seen people testing in excess of 50000 characters.  I have no idea why you would ever want such a long variable name.  The length is dependant on the memory available to Python. For practical programming purposes you dont need to worry about the length of your variable names in Python.  Pick something that is descriptive but keep it reasonable as you may end up typing it a lot ;-)As for the maximum storage size again that is dependant on the environment. In simple terms Pythons memory limits are determined by how much physical ram and virtual memory disk space your computer and operating system have available. You certainly shouldnt be bumping in to any of these limitations during this course., Resolved,1
